fect Strangers. Although commonly understood as a typical Hollywood practice, this book demonstrates how film remakes are, and always have been, a significant part of the European film culture and industry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aFilm remakeszEuropexHistory and criticism. 0aFilm remakes-History and criticism-Europe. 0aFilm remakes. 0aMotion pictures. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh1 aAraüna Baró, Núria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCuelenaere, Eduard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForrest, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoye, Stijn, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aJoye, Stijn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeitch, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMathilde Frank, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeir, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMunro, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNoordenbos, Boris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSanyal, Kamalika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSlugan, Mario, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Iain Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSouch, Irina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStewart, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVan Heuckelom, Kris, ec